2.10.25  11:25 pm   What does it all mean?

      i continue enjoy casually trying to explain this. the key word is 'casually', being that it is a totally endless process

2.10.25  11:21 pm   at the corner store is my favorite one of your songs and I know it's obviously about a corner store, but I feel like there's some deeper meaning that is just barely eluding me. (The rising price tags scene screams to me that I'm missing some crucial piece of context.) Could you clue me in on what it is pretty please?

      that's not about a corner store. let's be honest, the only thing i ever write songs about is the entire universe. technically that's the only thing i think about

2.10.25  11:18 pm   Do you remember the good old days back when a nickel only cost a dime?

      i don't recall that ever happening

2.10.25  11:13 pm   do you ever wish you could just turn your brain off

      not really

2.10.25  11:05 pm   how much bread am i allowed to eat

      as much as you want

2.10.25  10:52 pm   how to read

      if you have access to a large amount of written material with corresponding audio recordings of the same material, then you can have fun matching up which symbols repesent which words

2.10.25  10:26 pm   how are you doing? really.

      pretty good

2.10.25  9:42 pm   Can you please teach me how to be respected?

      no. my advice of course would be to do it in a whole new way. this strategy sounds great to me, but it may or may not be what you're into

2.10.25  9:00 pm   can squids dance?

      i don't see why not

2.10.25  8:35 pm   Sometimes I read people treating your behavior like some sort of inhuman cryptid. I personally think that's disrespectful, but of course I'm not you so...

how do you like that particular impression of your public persona?

      so far i've only heard it from you. it's ok, but you claim it's not good, so, in that case, thanks for that

2.10.25  8:23 pm   how many legs should camels have

      as many as they want

2.10.25  7:36 pm   What is your favorite wonder of the world, natural or otherwise?

      gravity

2.10.25  6:12 pm   do you believe in an objective good/evil

      i mostly know of that from storybooks

2.10.25  5:29 pm   Do you think I could if I tried my best?

      that is often the case

2.10.25  5:28 pm   I can read your mind, you are currently in a chair

      that may be true, but that's not what i was thinking about

2.10.25  5:23 pm   When you get asked a question that's a direct quote from one of your videos, does it ever feel like you're finding an answer to one of your own questions?

      no. if someone's quoting something, it's almost always done in a way that has no resemblance to the original context

2.10.25  5:01 pm   is the proof in the pudding?

      no, it's probably something like diproofzoade-15 nowadays

2.10.25  4:59 pm   Electrons or positrons, Mr. Wurtz? That is the question.

      i disagree, i think it looks more like just a phrase. or possibly an answer, to a question such as "what are some types of trons, etc"

2.10.25  4:47 pm   just wrote a poem, don't know what to do with it. what do you think of this anyway.

sometimes i wish to be a metallic crap.
No bones to preserve.
No flesh to feel.
No consciousness of the world.
No desire of sins.
No blasphemy of sort
No need of sleep
No religion of concern
No list of "things to achieve"

      this has a striking resemblance to those signs telling you what behaviors you must not do in this area

2.10.25  2:44 pm   What are your top five favorite films?

      if a film is any good, it should at least be good enough that it makes me forget about the rest of the list

2.10.25  2:12 pm   what's your favourite bird of prey? mine is the peregrine falcon

      i'm just realizing now how profound the phrase 'bird of prey' is for me, because i truly have no idea whether it means the bird is the prey or the preditor

2.10.25  1:44 pm   can genres be fun?

      sure. even more fun if you say it in French

2.10.25  1:41 pm   The great thing about objects is they usually draw their own boundary lines, that's what makes them objects. They're self defining. 

      i don't buy that for one second. ever seen a box of cookies? hopefully you get where i'm going with this

2.10.25  1:23 pm   Would you rather a question about you, or the world around? (Generally)

      the most important aspect of a question around here is that i did not compose the question

2.10.25  1:18 pm   What's the meaning behind your song "here comes the sun"?

      songwriting. that's pretty much the meaning behind all my songs, to be honest

2.10.25  12:35 pm   Why is my friend playing that game?

      it's really the same reason you play that other game

2.10.25  12:18 pm   What are your thoughts on when a a song contains a lyrical callback to a song previously written by the same artist (or, heck, a different artist)

      could happen

2.10.25  11:51 am   if the first thing you saw after reading this question got up, became sentient, and attacked you, how screwed would you be on a scale of one to ten?

      not nearly as scared as the first time i got next to that grand piano in the mario 64 ghost house

2.10.25  9:03 am   go eagles?

      they have certainly been known to go, in the past

2.10.25  3:33 am   Hey Bill, I was worried I may be getting parasocial obsession where I look to people named 'Bill' for life advice. What should I do about that?

      what exactly are the specific problems of doing that? i'm not saying there wouldn't be problems with doing that, but i'm just wondering which ones you had in mind

2.10.25  2:42 am   How do you make a nothing thing a something thing you know

      pretty much just by mentioning it

2.10.25  2:13 am   do you think the universe realized one day that it wanted to be there so then poof there it was?

      i think you'd have to be a little more specific in what exactly is included in the word 'universe'

2.10.25  1:23 am   I'm in a poetry class but I feel like everything I write is stupid. I've tried the strategy of writing stupid stuff on purpose, but then I feel creatively unfulfilled, like no one is taking my work or my abilities seriously. H e l p

      just for clarification, i'd like to know: why do you think you want to write something?

2.10.25  1:18 am   Why is the word "whose" also used for inanimate objects?

      sounds to me like a fear of witches. or at least a fear of saying witches

2.10.25  12:21 am   Why is the 7 train your favorite MTA subway line?

     just the purple alone would do it for me

      By the way, what did you think of the Hudson Yards station when it opened?

      seems like a versitile music video location

2.9.25  11:50 pm   Do you like Sonic?

      it's certainly a good name. the only problem is it's probably the name of a lot of different things, through the years. like "Checkers", or... "Luigi"

2.9.25  11:34 pm   How to interact with human beings in a normal way. I am secretly a tractor

      what does a human and a tractor have in common? if you play it within that area, you can act totally genuine while still achieving your goals

2.9.25  11:17 pm   What's your favorite cat toy?

      the earth

2.9.25  10:23 pm   How to make things go back to the way they once were?

      the real trick here is to recognize that right now is your only chance to experience things in the way things will soon once have been

2.9.25  9:45 pm   am i allowed to think?

      yes

2.9.25  8:52 pm   It dawned on me today that I'm further from achieving my personal goals than I was a decade ago, and I don't know how to cope with that

      i think you're just feeling a little scared right now. in a few moments from now i suspect you're going to be reminded of all kinds of progress you've made

2.9.25  8:22 pm   Everyday I try to sort my life out, but when the sun sets I find out it was me that was out of order. Do you know this feeling?

      it's good to have a balance where you are open to the possibility of either party being in order, or out of order, some of the time

2.9.25  7:55 pm   for sometime now, i'm inmagining myself hiring a band that is spontaneous at doing anything because i'm going to hire them to play your songs with me singing it. and i want them to recreate every bit of instruments as much as possible as that's what makes me groove with it. do you think it's a good idea? what advice do you have to give me if i'm going to execute this idea?

      in my opinion, creating exactly the instrumental parts of the recording would be a waste of time. it would be much more fruitful to absorb the song as a whole and then do it in your own way. have you ever painted a cat and painted all the individual hairs in exactly the same place as the original cat? the cat wouldn't even get why you did that

2.9.25  7:40 pm   what if cars could fly

      there would be a whole slew of new signs, infrastructure, and regulations

2.9.25  6:56 pm   What do you think about a G7 chord except I added a C# and Eb next to the D?

      although i'm not hearing any audio or actual context for this, i'm gonna go way out on a limb and say cancel the D. like if you told me you are going skiing with 3 skis, i'd say remove one of the skis

2.9.25  6:38 pm   Are you watching / going to watch the Super Bowl :3

      i think i will watch it later. those things age pretty well

2.9.25  5:57 pm   Is free will a concept explorable with scientific tools?

      that double slit experiment and some of those classic early quantum physics experiments are really what sealed the deal for me

2.9.25  5:38 pm   the one true religion?

      the..... truth

Sorry i fell asleep on the predictive text button.

      would it be fair for me to assume that there are some cars in your life?

      it's not intentionally weighted. but it's possible there may be some phenomenon that i've overlooked
